SHERRY’S SALE PRICES No Higher than a Year Ago!

We still offer the great 1952 and 1953 Clarets at low sale prices, based on our original cost, and not on the much higher replacement prices that now prevail on the Bordeaux market. Because of frost damage, there never has been such a short- age of wine in recent memory — almost as many empty barrels can be seen in the cellars as there are full ones. All of this adds up to an unwillingness of the vigneron to part with his precious stock. We advise acquisition before March 15th, before depletion, and before prices move upwards — and we would like to remind you that we will gladly store your purchases in our cool, underground cellars for as long as one year, free of charge.
